Subject: [PATCH 228/269] Changes:
 - Fixes security docs to suggest use of 'privacy' instead of 'auth-conf' for 'hbase.rpc.protection' property.
 - Changes SaslUtil to accept both kinds of values (privacy/integrity/authentication OR auth-conf/auth-int/auth) to be backward compatible with wrong doc.
 - Change thrift's property 'hbase.thrift.security.qop' to use same set of values(privacy/integrity/authentication) as '{hadoop,hbase}.rpc.protection'.  auth/auth-int/auth-conf are supported too for backward compat.
 - added exception throwing if configuration has wrong value.

